{
  "stem": "11744.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But the only thing we did was at least to try to work together during the Occupation.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And none of us knew how long it would last.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I mean, I don't know if any one of us would have gone on if we had known.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, moving around-- in Saint-Etienne for quite a long time, and when my in-laws were in the south of France, and the south of France was invaded by the Italians-- I mean, they were under Italian occupation.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it wasn't very bad.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But the only thing was that they had nothing to eat.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were absolutely starving because the south of France never produced anything but citrus fruits.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And you can't live on citrus fruit.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Everything came-- that went always regularly to the south of France-- the wheat and the barley and everything that you need, the flour, what you need to make a meal-- came from the north or from the east.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they were-- they were divided with the line.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There was a line in France between the occupied, so-called occupied zone an unoccupied zone.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Well, the nonoccupied zone still had Gestapo, but instead of being in uniform, they were in civilian clothes.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So they were even more dangerous.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But so they called me once in Saint-Etienne after my husband had been arrested for the third time.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He called me, and he said to me, the climate there is no good for you.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "You should really leave.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I understood very well what he meant.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He said, and the climate here in the south of France is not good for us.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "It would be nice if we could have a big house and be all together, so please try to find a place.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
